Document: CSGTorus3D
Path: godot/classes/class_csgtorus3d.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring a CSG torus shape in 3D space.

inner_radius (float): The inner radius of the torus. Default: 0.5. Methods: set_inner_radius(value: float) → void, get_inner_radius() → float.

material (Material): The material used to render the torus. Methods: set_material(value: Material) → void, get_material() → Material.

outer_radius (float): The outer radius of the torus. Default: 1.0. Methods: set_outer_radius(value: float) → void, get_outer_radius() → float.

ring_sides (int): The number of edges each ring of the torus is constructed of. Default: 6. Methods: set_ring_sides(value: int) → void, get_ring_sides() → int.

sides (int): The number of slices the torus is constructed of. Default: 8. Methods: set_sides(value: int) → void, get_sides() → int.

smooth_faces (bool): If true, the normals of the torus are set to give a smooth effect making the torus seem rounded. If false, the torus will have a flat shaded look. Default: true. Methods: set_smooth_faces(value: bool) → void, get_smooth_faces() → bool. Key Rule: Smooth faces enable rounded appearance, flat faces create angular look.